Hi Sarah,

Global stats are a useful general indicator, but personally I'd say
there's no substitute for looking at what your *own* site user base
are doing before you make the decision as to what resolution to
optimise for.

The sites I manage at the moment cater for a highly technical base,
the majority of whom are actually using 1280x1024 or above most of the
time - but we still designed to 800x600 to cater for the lowest
denominator (I'm not saying I agree with that choice, it was made
before I started...).

Cheers,

Rachael
