<POSTER> &quot;Simon R Jones&quot; &lt;simon.jo...@studio24.net&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-08-03T10:13:00 </POSTDATE>
We mostly design for 1024 wide (screen resolution) these days. Generally
speaking I think you're safe with this now, though it is advisable to check
your own screen resolution stats.

Another issue is the actual window size (as opposed to the screen
resolution) since many users don't view websites with their browser
full-screen. We had one project recently who wanted both 800x600 and
1024x768 (since many of their users viewed the site in a smaller window) so
we developed the site so it stretched between the two. See
http://www.red-gate.com/

best wishes,
Simon
</POST>
