I generally go for 970 min-width, then any max-width depending on the
application.

My opinion is that in 800x600 (or a resized window), users are aware
they need to scroll, so your site won't make a difference.  Bit
blinkered admittedly, but I use a few different resolutions myself
(extended desktop, 1440x900, 800x600 remote desktop and also Mini
Opera 4 on my K800i) and all seem pretty usable.
